I pushed some more changes, this now looks great.

@kmill, could you check the unexpander / use of `default_instance` is reasonable?

I pushed some more changes, this now looks great.

@kmill, could you check the unexpander / use of `default_instance` is reasonable?
It would be nice if `√2` elaborated to a `Real` in the absense of any other information, in the same way that `2` is by default a nat...
And it would be nice to have a delaborator.
Resolved by adding `default_instance` and an unexpander.
I would guess that you can use `notation3` for some of these to get a delaborator
Writing one by hand as I did below probably makes more sense anyway.
Just noting that this PR is currently a step backwards WRT delaborator support.

If the superscript is complicated (even with just `NthRoot.nthRoot (2*n) x`) it won't pretty print correctly. I think restricting to just number literals and identifiers should handle the common cases:
```suggestion
@[app_unexpander NthRoot.nthRoot]
def NthRoot.unexpander : Lean.PrettyPrinter.Unexpander
  | `($_ 2 $a) => `(√$a)
  | `($_ 3 $a) => `(∛$a)
  | `($_ 4 $a) => `(∜$a)
  | `($_ $n:num $a) | `($_ $n:ident $a) => `($n:superscript √$a)
  | _ => throw ()
```
